Borton's reflection method

![](data:image/png;base64,)

What - the event you are reflecting on

So what? - analysing what was important about the event

Now what? - outlines how learning from the event will be applied in future

## Kolb

1. Concrete experience. Factual description
2. Reflective observation. What went well? What not so well? Why did things go the way they did? What could you do differently?
3. Abstract conceptualisation. Summarise reflection.
4. Active experimentation. Try news ways to tackle challenges.
